Colombian Stock Movers: Pacific Rubiales, Cementos Argos Rise

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-02-22T21:28:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/colombian-stock-movers-pacific-rubiales-cementos-argos-rise.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index increased 0.2 percent to 14,289.45, while
the Colcap Index gained 0.2 percent to 1,661.43.    Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp . (PREC CB), the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, rose 1.7 percent
to 59,820 pesos. Oil surged to the highest level in more than
two years as violence intensified in  Libya , the holder of
Africa’s largest crude reserves.    Cementos Argos SA  (CEMARGOS CB), Colombia’s largest cement
maker and exporter, climbed 1.2 percent to 10,520 pesos.
Confidence among U.S. consumers rose in February to a three-year
high, exceeding forecasts, as more Americans predicted the
economy and their incomes will grow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
